claim.claim-text:
A robot cleaner comprising:
a body (10) provided with a suction portion (14);
an auxiliary front wheel (20) disposed at the body (10);
a main wheel (40) disposed at a rear side of the auxiliary front wheel (20) and arranged such that a height of the main wheel (40) is variable with respect to the body (10); and
a driving unit (50) to lower or raise the main wheel (40) with respect to the body (10),
wherein the driving unit (50) lowers the main wheel (40) when the auxiliary front wheel (20) enters a stepped portion (80).

A method for controlling a robot cleaner comprising the steps of:
determining whether an auxiliary front wheel (20) installed at a body (10) of the robot cleaner enters a stepped portion (80);
lowering a main wheel (40) of the robot cleaner with respect to the body (10) when the auxiliary front wheel (20) enters the stepped portion (80);
determining whether the main wheel (40) enters the stepped portion (80): and
raising the main wheel (40) with respect to the body (10) when the main wheel (40) enters the stepped portion (80).
